cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper discusses the limitations and problems of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) in learning the target distribution of images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes theoretical and empirical analysis, which suggests the possibility of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a sub-category. Finally, the proposed methods to mitigate the anomalous generalization of GANs involve optimization techniques, which could be related to cs.GR (Graphics).
